parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and failure of brake lines can cause the brake pedal to go to the floor, leading to a complete loss of brakes, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
and the vehicle takes longer to stop or fails to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unexpected engagement of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to take longer to stop or fail to stop, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS system engages at low speeds
causing the brake pedal to vibrate
and the vehicle takes longer to stop or fails to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause the speedometer, tachometer, and other gauges to malfunction or fail, leading to a loss of critical information for the driver, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The speedometer and tachometer may malfunction or fail
or not functioning at all. Other gauges

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the blower motor resistor can cause the blower motor to malfunction, leading to a loss of heating and cooling functionality, which can be a safety concern in extreme temperatures.
symptoms: The blower motor may not function or may malfunction
causing the heating and cooling system to fail.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The reduced engine power can cause the vehicle to suddenly lose power, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving on the highway.
symptoms: The vehicle may suddenly go into "reduced engine power" mode
causing a loss of power and acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause loss of control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Clunking or rattling noise in the steering column
and leakage of power steering fluid.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause loss of control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: and failure of the brake system to respond properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel injectors can cause reduced engine power, stalling, and difficulty starting the engine, which can lead to accidents or strand the driver.
The failure of the transmission can cause loss of control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Clunking or banging noise in the transmission

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of undercarriage components can cause failure of the power steering, brake, and transmission systems, leading to loss of control of the vehicle and accidents.
